    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-01T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="515"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4508: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin (<persName corresp="#p_LFP1"
                            type="from">Lockhart</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-01T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 1, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 1—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 1, 3 p.m. The <hi rend="italic">Tencho Mavu</hi> from Dairen,
                            specially chartered by Japanese military, landed 550 rifles, 12
                            fieldpieces, 80 machine guns and 3,150 cases of ammunition at Tangku
                            yesterday and returned immediately to Dairen. The landing of so much
                            Japanese war material under present circumstances has caused great
                            concern at Tangku and considerable speculation at Tientsin. There are
                            reported to be 2,000 Chinese troops at Tangku, 500 at Hsinho and 500 at
                            Taku and 150 Japanese troops at Tangku. Martial law is being enforced at
                            night at Tangku.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Department and Shanghai.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LFP1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
